<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-182-740  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 182 740.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Feb 26 1990 v36 n1798 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple plans to shut down distribution/support center. (located inChicago)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lapedus, Mark.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple, in the midst of a company-wide reorganization, will closeone of its three US distribution/support centers and lay off threepercent of its workforce, or about 400 employees.andP;  The centerscheduled for closure by Apr 1990 is located in Chicago.andP;  Othercenters in Charlotte, NC, and Sunnyvale, CA, will now be overseenby a financial executive instead of Apple's top domestic salesexecutive.andP;  Other reorganization plans include: the closure ofnon-California field service operations and elimination of severalundisclosed projects within the company.andP;  Apple recently madesweeping changes in its structure and style: the computer companyreshuffled its management ranks, cut its 1990 sales growthprojection by more than 50 percent, announced a cost-cutting planto eliminate several hundred jobs and took a related $20.5 millioncharge against earnings.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (management).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Topic:     ReorganizationComputer industryPlant shutdownsLayoff.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>